OL,3,CBlue Islands' suspension of operations
OL,4,C'a shambles', says travel expert
OL,6,FMr Calder believes this situation
OL,7,Fcould have been handled differently,
OL,8,Fexplaining: "It is possible for a
OL,9,Fregional airline not simply to just
OL,10,Fshut down.
OL,12,F"We've seen, for instance, the German
OL,13,Fairline Air Berlin was allowed to
OL,14,Fcontinue the season's flights in order
OL,15,Fto have an orderly wind-down of the
OL,16,Foperation.
OL,18,F"This is much better for the staff of
OL,19,Fan airline, much better for
OL,20,Fpassengers, and a much better look for
OL,21,Fthe Channel Islands."
